Vim Editor Commands for DevOps

These are some of the most commonly used Vim editor commands during DevOps work. Every command below includes what it does and when we use it.

Navigation CommandsG

Moves the cursor to the last line of the file.

G

Moves the cursor to the first line of the file.

gg

Moves the cursor to line number 3.

3gg

Moves the cursor to line number 10.

10gg


Moves the cursor to the middle of the screen.

M

Moves to line number 4.

:4

Moves to line number 9.

:9

Copy Commands

Copies the current line.

yy


Copies 5 lines starting from the current line.

5yy

Paste Commandsp

Pastes the copied content below the current line.

p

Pastes the copied content 10 times.

10p

Delete Commands3dd

Deletes 3 lines.

3dd


Deletes 5 lines.

5dd

Undo and Redo Commands

Undo the last action.

u


Redo the last undone action.

Ctrl + r

Search Commands/folder

Searches forward for the word "folder".

/folder
  
Searches backward for the word "folder".

?folder

Replace Commands:

Replaces the first occurrence of "folder" with "aws" in each line.

:%s/folder/aws

Replaces all occurrences of "folder" with "aws" in the entire file.

:%s/folder/aws/g

Insert Mode Commandsinsert mode

Vim has different modes. Insert mode is used to type text.

Enters insert mode before the cursor.

i

Enters insert mode at the end of the line.

A


Enters insert mode at the beginning of the line.

I


Opens a new line below and enters insert mode.

o


Opens a new line above and enters insert mode.

O


Exits insert mode.

esc

Save and Quit Commands:W

Saves the file.

:w

Quits the editor.

:q

Quits without saving changes.

:q!

Forces save.

:w!

Saves and quits.

:wq
  
Forces save and quit.

:wq!
